        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="423" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.002/1–2348</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-23">January 23,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Notes on Cabinet Meeting, Friday, January</hi> 23, 1948, 10
                    A. M.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>I referred again to the matter of dismantling of the plants for reparations,
                    which was not completed at the previous meeting. Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RKC1">Royall</persName> and I recommended the approval of the
                    general outline for procedure covered in the memorandum of January 15.<note n="1" xml:id="d423fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_708">p. 708</ref>.</note>
                    Secretaries <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KJA1">Krug</persName> opposed any dismantling whatsoever on
                    grounds that appeared to be almost identical with those expressed in the
                    Congressional questioning of Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RKC1">Royall</persName> and which contained numerous inaccuracies in information.
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RKC1">Royall</persName> carried the brunt of the
                    discussion, which was thrown over to next week because of the shortage of time.
                    I emphasized particularly that the matter should be taken up promptly with the
                    Senate Foreign Relations Committee and there was general agreement that this
                    should be done.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LRA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert</hi> A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
